10 underrepresented students, and nontraditional age students; and
11 (e) Facilitating credit hour accumulation and transfer of students from KCTCS to
12 four (4) year postsecondary institutions.
13 (3) (a) The General Assembly hereby declares these goals can best be accomplished
14 by implementing a comprehensive funding model for the allocation of state
15 general fund appropriations for postsecondary institution operations that
16 aligns the Commonwealth's investments in postsecondary education with the
17 Commonwealth's postsecondary education policy goals and objectives.
18 (b) The General Assembly further recognizes that priority for state general fund
19 appropriations for postsecondary institutions should be given to each
20 institution's funding floor over appropriations to the performance fund. For
21 purposes of this section, "funding floor" means an institution's fiscal year
22 2020-2021 general fund appropriation included in 2020 Ky. Acts ch. 92, plus
23 any fiscal year 2020-2021 distribution from the performance fund, and minus
24 fiscal year 2020-2021 debt service on bonds and appropriations for mandated
25 programs.
26 (4) This section establishes a comprehensive funding model for the public
27 postsecondary education system to be implemented by the Council on
