15 (13) (a) The postsecondary education performance fund is hereby established as an
16 appropriation unit to support improvement in the operations of the public
17 postsecondary institutions and achievement of the Commonwealth's education
18 policy goals and workforce development priorities. General fund moneys may
19 be appropriated by the General Assembly to this fund for distribution to the
20 public postsecondary institutions in amounts determined through the
21 comprehensive funding model created in this section.
22 (b) Any balance in the performance fund at the close of any fiscal year shall not
23 lapse but shall be carried forward to the next fiscal year and be continuously
24 appropriated for the purposes specified in this section. A general statement
25 that all continuing appropriations are repealed, discontinued, or suspended
26 shall not operate to repeal, discontinue, or suspend this fund or to repeal this
27 action.
